poems.content:
She came like spring,
With a crown of flowers;
She passed by like summer,
With sun-like eyes,
Reminding me of sunshine;
Sweating like monsoon,
She made my heart wet like rains of June;
Melodiously rustling maple leaves,
She walked into the autumn,
With skin like cotton;
She cooled off like pre-winter,
Diving into the river;
She hushed with ease,
Like winter breeze,
She smiled at me,
And got my heart seized.

They all were luxurious houses,
But she was my home;
They all were roses,
But she was my garden;
They all were galaxies,
But she was my earth;
They all were melodies,
But she was my harmony;
They all were the brightest stars,
But she was my moon;
They all were rains,
But she was hurricane;
They all were my likes,
But she is my love.

Let's gaze,
but not speak;
Let's speak,
but not express;
Let's express,
but not understand;
Let's understand,
but not react;
Let's react,
but not smile;
Let's smile,
but not hold hands;
Let's hold hands,
but not ask names;
Let's ask names,
but not stories;
Let's ask stories,
but not share;
Let's share,
but not commit;
Let's commit,
but not promise;
Let's promise,
but not forever;
Let's aim forever,
but in our silent endeavour.

My words like wine,
aging just fine;
Crafting poetic vine,
whenever I see thine;

Awhile burns my heart with a shine,
a shine I couldn't confine;
Praying for thy next sight to the divine,
hoping for hearts to someday align;

Lost in city of precious time,
I whine,
to seek shelter in thy shrine;

Searching for a universal sign,
to pursue my love towards thine,
while facing the world defining my love as crime;

A genuine wish of mine,
to tune in into our heartbeats chime;
Wrapping up my love's zine,
with an ask towards thine:

Will you be mine,
to complete my life's rhyme?
